[3
Date: 2 Aug 2000 10:48:49 -0700
From: Nikos Gurfield <ngurfiag@co.san-diego.ca.us>

In response to the spectrum of susceptible species to EEE mentioned in this
posting, a small correction would be that some farm animals, i.e., cows and
pigs, are susceptible to EEE infection.
1. Eastern equine encephalomyelitis in an adult cow. Vet Pathol. 1992
Jul;29(4):361-3.
2. Eastern equine encephalomyelitis virus infection in swine. J Am Vet Med
Assoc. 1994 Oct 1;205(7):1014-6.
3. Prevalence of exposure to eastern equine encephalomyelitis virus in
domestic and feral swine in Georgia. J Vet Diagn Invest. 1996 Oct;8(4):481-4.
--
Nikos Gurfield, DVM
Office of the County Veterinarian, San Diego
<ngurfiag@co.san-diego.ca.us>
