[4
Date: 2 Aug 2000 19:51:59 -0400
From: James Pearson <JPEARSON@dgs.state.va.us>
The recent posting (8/1) [East. equine encephalitis, horses - USA
(Virginia) 2000.3063 based on an article in the Virginia Pilot contains an
error. [An Outer Banks woman died of EEE, while Outer Banks is actually in
North Carolina. The laboratory results reported by the Virginia State
Laboratory (Division of Consolidated Laboratory Services) were negative for
EEE by EIA (Enzyme Immuno Assay). The results were also confirmed negative.
We forwarded samples to Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC),
and they concurred with our results. The screening assay (MRL Diagnostic
Company) performed in a private laboratory was positive for EEE.
--
Dr. Jim Pearson, Director
Virginia Division of Consolidated Laboratory Services
Richmond, VA 23219
<JPEARSON@dgs.state.va.us>
